1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:02,460
[narrator] 
NOW THE STORY

2
00:00:02,460 --> 00:00:04,212
OF A WEALTHY FAMILY 
WHO LOST EVERYTHING...

3
00:00:04,212 --> 00:00:05,630
AND THE ONE SON 
WHO HAD NO CHOICE...

4
00:00:05,630 --> 00:00:07,173
BUT TO KEEP THEM ALL TOGETHER.

5
00:00:12,678 --> 00:00:14,680
IT'S ARRESTED DEVELOPMENT.

6
00:00:19,185 --> 00:00:21,229
[narrator] 
THIS IS MICHAEL BLUTH.

7
00:00:21,229 --> 00:00:23,814
RIGHT NOW HE'S 
TAKING HIS SON, GEORGE MICHAEL,

8
00:00:23,814 --> 00:00:25,566
TO START A NEW LIFE IN ARIZONA.

9
00:00:25,566 --> 00:00:28,444
- PHOENIX, ARIZONA, HUH? 
THIS IS IT, BOY.

10
00:00:28,444 --> 00:00:30,530
WE ARE FREE.

11
00:00:30,530 --> 00:00:32,698
WE'RE GONNA FOLLOW 
OUR DREAMS, YOU KNOW?

12
00:00:32,698 --> 00:00:34,159
AND THE BEST PART OF IT?

13
00:00:34,159 --> 00:00:36,077
NOT WORKIN' 
FOR THE FAMILY ANYMORE.

14
00:00:36,077 --> 00:00:39,414
- YEAH, BUT DON'T-- DON'T YOU 
ALWAYS SAY "FAMILY FIRST"?

15
00:00:39,414 --> 00:00:40,706
- YES, I DO.

16
00:00:40,706 --> 00:00:44,210
BUT THAT IS 
NOT A FAMILY, OKAY?

17
00:00:44,210 --> 00:00:46,296
THEY'RE A BUNCH 
OF GREEDY, SELFISH PEOPLE

18
00:00:46,296 --> 00:00:48,256
WHO HAVE OUR NOSE.

19
00:00:48,256 --> 00:00:50,966
AND AUNT LINDSAY. 
- SHE'S NOT MY REAL AUNT?

20
00:00:50,966 --> 00:00:52,843
- NOT A REAL NOSE.

21
00:00:52,843 --> 00:00:55,221
GOT A PICTURE OF HER WHEN 
SHE'S 14 IN A SWIMMING CAP.

22
00:00:55,221 --> 00:00:57,348
SHE LOOKS LIKE A FALCON.

23
00:00:57,348 --> 00:00:59,517
SPENT AN ENTIRE YEAR LIVING 
IN THAT STUPID MODEL HOME

24
00:00:59,517 --> 00:01:01,018
WITH THOSE PEOPLE,

25
00:01:01,018 --> 00:01:02,978
AND ALL THEY DID 
WAS LIE TO US.

26
00:01:02,978 --> 00:01:04,855
[narrator] 
THE MOST RECENT LIE WAS

27
00:01:04,855 --> 00:01:07,067
MICHAEL'S FATHER HAD HAD 
A HEART ATTACK WHILE IN PRISON.

28
00:01:07,067 --> 00:01:09,944
- WE LOST HIM. 
[sobbing]

29
00:01:09,944 --> 00:01:11,529
[narrator] 
WHAT THE DOCTOR MEANT TO SAY

30
00:01:11,529 --> 00:01:13,448
WAS THAT GEORGE SR. HAD ESCAPED,

31
00:01:13,448 --> 00:01:15,325
A FEAT HE'D ACCOMPLISHED

32
00:01:15,325 --> 00:01:17,410
BY USING THE FAMILY'S PORTABLE 
STAIRWAY VEHICLE.

33
00:01:19,620 --> 00:01:21,581
- I'D LOVE TO SEE THE LOOK 
ON THEIR FACES RIGHT NOW.

34
00:01:21,581 --> 00:01:22,790
[chuckles]

35
00:01:22,790 --> 00:01:24,459
"WHERE'D HE GO?"

36
00:01:24,459 --> 00:01:26,336
- OR THEY-- THEY THINK WE'RE 
JUST HEADED HOME.

37
00:01:26,336 --> 00:01:28,588
ACTUALLY, YOU KNOW, 
THAT'S KIND OF WHAT I THOUGHT...

38
00:01:28,588 --> 00:01:30,923
UNTIL I HEARD ABOUT 
ALL THAT PHOENIX STUFF.

39
00:01:30,923 --> 00:01:32,842
[narrator] 
MICHAEL WAS CONCERNED THAT THE

40
00:01:32,842 --> 00:01:34,719
FULL IMPACT OF HIS DEPARTURE..

41
00:01:34,719 --> 00:01:36,346
MIGHT HAVE BEEN LOST 
ON HIS FAMILY.

42
00:01:36,346 --> 00:01:38,055
[phone beeping]

43
00:01:38,055 --> 00:01:40,099
- HELLO. WHO IS THIS? 
- YES, THIS IS DR. BLUMEN.

44
00:01:40,099 --> 00:01:42,685
I'M CALLING 
REGARDING MICHAEL BLUTH.

45
00:01:42,685 --> 00:01:46,772
- MICHAEL! PHONE! 
[beeps]

46
00:01:46,772 --> 00:01:48,774
- THEY THINK 
WE'RE STILL THERE.

47
00:01:48,774 --> 00:01:51,152
WE'RE GOIN' BACK.

48
00:01:51,152 --> 00:01:54,239
[phone line beeping] 
HEY, MOM. ANY MESSAGES?

49
00:01:54,239 --> 00:01:55,531
- NONE.

50
00:01:55,531 --> 00:01:57,117
[recorded voice, 
indistinct]

51
00:01:57,117 --> 00:01:58,909
- NO, THERE WAS A MESSAGE.

52
00:01:58,909 --> 00:02:00,953
IT WAS ABOUT MY HEALTH, 
BUT IT DOESN'T MATTER.

53
00:02:00,953 --> 00:02:02,913
MY SON AND I-- 
[horn blasts]

54
00:02:02,913 --> 00:02:05,583
- BUSTER, WHAT ARE YOU DOING 
WITH MOTHER'S RAPE HORN?

55
00:02:05,583 --> 00:02:08,211
YES, I HAVE A RAPE HORN, 
MICHAEL, BECAUSE YOU

56
00:02:08,211 --> 00:02:10,713
TOOK AWAY MY MACE.

57
00:02:10,713 --> 00:02:13,841
- YEAH, LIKE ANYONE 
WOULD WANT TO "R" HER.

58
00:02:13,841 --> 00:02:16,302
- THIS IS WHAT I'M TALKING 
ABOUT, MICHAEL.

59
00:02:16,302 --> 00:02:18,471
NOW THAT YOUR FATHER HAS 
DESERTED US, BUSTER'S BECOME

60
00:02:18,471 --> 00:02:20,723
IMPOSSIBLE TO CONTROL.

61
00:02:20,723 --> 00:02:22,517
SUDDENLY HE'S 
TOO MUCH OF A BIG SHOT

62
00:02:22,517 --> 00:02:23,768
TO BRUSH MOTHER'S HAIR.

63
00:02:23,768 --> 00:02:25,436
- WELL, I'M NOT HE--

64
00:02:28,231 --> 00:02:31,734
I'M NOT HELPING YOU 
WITH BUSTER ANYMORE.

65
00:02:31,734 --> 00:02:34,529
I'M NOT HELPING ANYONE 
WITH ANYTHING.

66
00:02:34,529 --> 00:02:37,490
I CAME HERE TO TELL YOU 
THAT MY SON AND I--

67
00:02:37,490 --> 00:02:39,325
[blender whirring]

68
00:02:42,995 --> 00:02:44,830
[narrator] 
GEORGE MICHAEL, MEANWHILE, WAS

69
00:02:44,830 --> 00:02:46,291
APPROACHED BY HIS COUSIN MAEBY.

70
00:02:46,291 --> 00:02:48,000
- SO, YOU'RE REALLY 
LEAVIN', HUH?

71
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,544
HAVE YOU TOLD 
YOUR GIRLFRIEND, BLAND?

72
00:02:49,544 --> 00:02:51,254
I MEAN, ANN.

73
00:02:51,254 --> 00:02:53,088
- SHE'S NOT MY GIRLFRIEND, 
AND SHE'S NOT BLAND.

74
00:02:53,088 --> 00:02:54,340
- REALLY?

75
00:02:54,340 --> 00:02:56,050
BECAUSE, I MEAN, 
UNDER HER SCHOOL PICTURE

76
00:02:56,050 --> 00:02:57,760
IT SAID "NOT PICTURED."

77
00:02:57,760 --> 00:02:59,262
- OKAY, THEY PRINTED A 
RETRACTION

78
00:02:59,262 --> 00:03:01,096
IN THE SPRING SUPPLEMENT.

79
00:03:01,096 --> 00:03:03,224
AND, YEAH, SHE WAS REALLY 
LOOKIN' FORWARD TO SEEING ME

80
00:03:03,224 --> 00:03:04,600
IN MY UNCLE SAM OUTFIT...

81
00:03:04,600 --> 00:03:06,311
IN THAT GET OUT THE VOTE 
ASSEMBLY TOMORROW.

82
00:03:06,311 --> 00:03:08,271
- WASN'T THAT SUPPOSED TO BE 
BEFORE THE ELECTION?

83
00:03:08,271 --> 00:03:10,606
- THEY HAD TO POSTPONE IT WHEN 
THAT FOREIGN EXCHANGE STUDENT

84
00:03:10,606 --> 00:03:11,774
