"I'VE MADE A HUGE MISTAKE,"

115
00:04:19,425 --> 00:04:22,637
YOU CAN BAIL YOURSELF OUT 
NEXT TIME.

116
00:04:22,637 --> 00:04:24,430
- I'VE NEVER ADMITTED 
TO A MISTAKE.

117
00:04:24,430 --> 00:04:26,682
WHAT WOULD I 
HAVE MADE A MISTAKE ABOUT?

118
00:04:26,682 --> 00:04:28,893
- LINDSAY, INSTEAD OF SLEEPING 
IN TWIN BEDS, YOU AND YOUR

119
00:04:28,893 --> 00:04:31,103
HUSBAND TAKE THE MASTER BEDROOM.

120
00:04:31,103 --> 00:04:32,730
IT'S NOT LIKE 
YOU'VE NEVER COME TO ME

121
00:04:32,730 --> 00:04:34,315
WITH YOUR MARITAL PROBLEMS,

122
00:04:34,315 --> 00:04:35,775
SAYING, 
"OH, HELP ME, MICHAEL.

123
00:04:35,775 --> 00:04:37,109
I THINK MY HUSBAND MIGHT BE A--"

124
00:04:37,109 --> 00:04:38,152
[horn blasts]

125
00:04:38,152 --> 00:04:39,236
- OHH! 
[laughing]

126
00:04:39,236 --> 00:04:40,321
WELL-- IT'S--

127
00:04:40,321 --> 00:04:42,365
[groans] 
- HERE WE GO.

128
00:04:42,365 --> 00:04:44,534
[narrator] 
AND SO, ONCE AGAIN,

129
00:04:44,534 --> 00:04:46,952
THE GUYS WERE ON THEIR WAY TO 
PHOENIX, NEVER TO LOOK BACK.

130
00:04:46,952 --> 00:04:48,579
- [low voice] 
IT'S JUST THE LAB CALLING.

131
00:04:48,579 --> 00:04:50,831
WE'LL GIVE HIM THE BAD NEWS 
IN PHOENIX.

132
00:04:50,831 --> 00:04:53,418
THEY KNOW WE'RE GONE. 
- GREAT.

133
00:04:53,418 --> 00:04:57,338
YOU DID SAY PHOENIX AGAIN, 
BUT WHAT DO WE CARE?

134
00:04:57,338 --> 00:04:59,089
- SORRY.

135
00:04:59,089 --> 00:05:01,842
- NOW, DO YOU WANT TO STEER, 
OR ARE YOU TOO OLD TO SIT

136
00:05:01,842 --> 00:05:03,511
ON YOUR POP'S LAP AND DRIVE?

137
00:05:07,765 --> 00:05:09,850
- I THINK I MIGHT BE.

138
00:05:09,850 --> 00:05:11,811
- OKAY.

139
00:05:11,811 --> 00:05:15,606
[siren winding down]

140
00:05:21,779 --> 00:05:23,448
- CAR'S REGISTERED 
TO GEORGE BLUTH,

141
00:05:23,448 --> 00:05:25,825
SO WE HAD TO CHECK.

142
00:05:25,825 --> 00:05:27,535
BUT HE'S BEEN CAUGHT, 
SO YOU'RE FREE TO GO.

143
00:05:27,535 --> 00:05:29,495
- HE'S BEEN CAUGHT?

144
00:05:29,495 --> 00:05:31,163
[narrator] 
MICHAEL KNEW IF HE WENT BACK

145
00:05:31,163 --> 00:05:32,748
TO SEE HIS FATHER,

146
00:05:32,748 --> 00:05:34,625
HE WOULD ONLY END UP 
SAYING SOMETHING HURTFUL.

147
00:05:34,625 --> 00:05:36,752
- WE'RE GOIN' BACK.

148
00:05:36,752 --> 00:05:39,046
[narrator] 
IN FACT, THE POLICE ONLY THOUGHT

149
00:05:39,046 --> 00:05:40,631
THEY'D ARRESTED GEORGE SR.

150
00:05:40,631 --> 00:05:43,008
- DO YOU HAVE ANY COOKIES 
WITH NO PRESERVATIVES?

151
00:05:43,008 --> 00:05:44,552
[narrator] 
BUT HAD GOTTEN HIS TWIN

152
00:05:44,552 --> 00:05:46,053
BROTHER, OSCAR, INSTEAD.

153
00:05:46,053 --> 00:05:47,388
- OSCAR! A TALL TEA 
FOR OSCAR!

154
00:05:47,388 --> 00:05:48,889
- YEAH!

155
00:05:48,889 --> 00:05:51,434
- OH, GOOD GRIEF. 
IT'S OSCAR.

156
00:05:51,434 --> 00:05:54,019
- OH, THANK GOD YOU'VE COME. 
[sighs]

157
00:05:54,019 --> 00:05:55,938
[narrator] 
LUCILLE HAD A RELATIONSHIP

158
00:05:55,938 --> 00:05:58,023
WITH OSCAR YEARS EARLIER,

159
00:05:58,023 --> 00:05:59,692
WHICH SHE WAS NOT EAGER 
TO REKINDLE.

160
00:05:59,692 --> 00:06:00,860
- WHAT IS WRONG WITH YOU?

161
00:06:00,860 --> 00:06:02,570
THE BOY IS HERE. 
- OH.

162
00:06:02,570 --> 00:06:06,616
THEY SAID MY FATHER WAS HERE. 
- DID THEY?

163
00:06:08,909 --> 00:06:11,954
- LET'S GET OUT OF HERE. 
- WHAT-WHAT ABOUT OSCAR?

164
00:06:11,954 --> 00:06:14,457
- YES. THEY IMPOUNDED MY, UH-- 
MY HUMBLE TRAILER.

165
00:06:14,457 --> 00:06:16,501
- YOU'LL STAY WITH US. 
- NO, HE WON'T.

166
00:06:16,501 --> 00:06:18,753
- YOU'RE THE ONE WHO SAYS 
I NEED A FATHER FIGURE.

167
00:06:18,753 --> 00:06:22,131
- YES. 
A FATHER FIGURE.

168
00:06:24,133 --> 00:06:26,969
- FINE. BUT YOU'RE NOT 
SLEEPING IN MY BED.

169
00:06:26,969 --> 00:06:29,430
- OKAY. 
- OKAY. YEAH.

170
00:06:30,765 --> 00:06:32,349
[narrator] 
SOON, MICHAEL ARRIVED

171
00:06:32,349 --> 00:06:34,226
TO CLAIM HIS FATHER...

172
00:06:34,226 --> 00:06:36,395
AND WAS MET BY THE FAMILY 
ATTORNEY, BARRY ZUCKERKORN.

173
00:06:36,395 --> 00:06:37,563
- HMM.

174
00:06:37,563 --> 00:06:39,064
- NO, I KNOW, 
I KNOW, I KNOW.

175
00:06:39,064 --> 00:06:41,609
EVERYBODY SAYS LEAVE IT ALONE, 
LEAVE IT ALONE.

176
00:06:41,609 --> 00:06:42,943
DOES THIS LOOK CONTAGIOUS 
TO YOU?

177
00:06:42,943 --> 00:06:44,319
HEY, KIDDO.

178
00:06:44,319 --> 00:06:46,906
ALL RIGHT. 
IT WASN'T YOUR FATHER.

179
00:06:46,906 --> 00:06:48,282
IT WAS YOUR UNCLE.

180
00:06:48,282 --> 00:06:49,867
I RAN INTO THEM 
AS THEY WERE LEAVING.

181
00:06:49,867 --> 00:06:52,077
- THERE HE IS! 
- GOT YA!

182
00:06:52,077 --> 00:06:55,330
- OH, FOR GOD'S SAKE. 
- [grunts] YEAH!

183
00:06:55,330 --> 00:06:57,374
- I ONLY CAME BACK TO TELL HIM 
I WAS LEAVING, SO I GUESS

184
00:06:57,374 --> 00:06:59,043
IT'S TIME TO GO, SON.

185
00:06:59,043 --> 00:07:01,587
- WHERE YOU GOING? 
- WE CAN'T TELL YOU.

186
00:07:01,587 --> 00:07:04,339
- NO, NO. WE CAN TELL BARRY. 
WE'RE GOING TO PHOENIX.

187
00:07:04,339 --> 00:07:06,676
- OH, I WISH YOU 
HADN'T HAVE SAID THAT.

188
00:07:06,676 --> 00:07:08,135
AS YOUR LAWYER, 
I HAVE TO INFORM YOU

189
00:07:08,135 --> 00:07:09,637
YOU CANNOT LEAVE THE STATE.

190
00:07:09,637 --> 00:07:11,431
WITH YOUR FATHER GONE, 
THEY WANT TO HOLD YOU.

191
00:07:11,431 --> 00:07:13,015
- M-ME?

192
00:07:13,015 --> 00:07:14,600
- THEY'RE GOING TO 
INDICT YOU TOMORROW.

193
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:16,393
ALL YOU HAVE TO DO 
IS COME UP WITH THE BAIL.

194
00:07:16,393 --> 00:07:18,103
TAKE IT OUT OF THE BUSINESS.

195
00:07:18,103 --> 00:07:19,939
- BUT I-- I CAN'T. 
I QUIT.

196
00:07:19,939 --> 00:07:22,107
I DON'T WANT TO FOLLOW 
IN MY FATHER'S FOOTSTEPS.

197
00:07:22,107 --> 00:07:24,485
- THEN YOU MIGHT WIND UP 
ON HIS COT.

198
00:07:24,485 --> 00:07:27,697
OH, MAN, I WISH YOU 
HADN'T SAID PHOENIX.

199
00:07:27,697 --> 00:07:29,574
WOW.

200
00:07:32,910 --> 00:07:34,620
[narrator] 
MICHAEL HAD JUST FOUND OUT

201
00:07:34,620 --> 00:07:35,871
HE COULDN'T LEAVE THE STATE...

202
00:07:35,871 --> 00:07:37,457
UNLESS HE CAME UP WITH BAIL.

203
00:07:37,457 --> 00:07:39,124
- OKAY, LISTEN. 
I'M GONNA GET

204
00:07:39,124 --> 00:07:41,085
THE COMPANY CHECKBOOK 
AND DON'T TELL THE FAMILY.

205
00:07:41,085 --> 00:07:43,128
WE CAN'T GIVE THEM 
THE SATISFACTION OF TELLING THEM

206
00:07:43,128 --> 00:07:44,589
THAT I NEED MONEY, OKAY?

207
00:07:44,589 --> 00:07:46,716
DO YOU REMEMBER WHAT WE 
SAY ABOUT THE FAMILY?

208
00:07:46,716 --> 00:07:48,342
- IT'S NOT AUNT LINDSAY'S NOSE.

209
00:07:48,342 --> 00:07:50,052
- YES, BUT NO.

210
00:07:50,052 --> 00:07:51,971
DON'T-- DON'T TELL THEM 
THAT WE WERE GOIN' TO--

211
00:07:51,971 --> 00:07:53,598
- WE SAY WE DON'T 
NEED THEM. HMM?

212
00:07:53,598 --> 00:07:55,057
- OH. YEAH. OKAY.

213
00:07:55,057 --> 00:07:57,602
THE NEW ONE. 
I DIDN'T--

214
00:07:57,602 --> 00:07:58,978
[tv: woman] 
IT COMES FROM KNOWING

215
