224
00:08:17,788 --> 00:08:21,667
[tv: woman] 
TOGETHER, TWO, THREE, FOUR.

225
00:08:21,667 --> 00:08:24,336
RELEASE, TWO, THREE, FOUR. 
- OH, LINDSAY.

226
00:08:24,336 --> 00:08:25,880
[tv off]

227
00:08:25,880 --> 00:08:29,174
UH, WELL, 
THIS IS EXCITING.

228
00:08:29,174 --> 00:08:30,760
- FINALLY WE CAN BE 
A NORMAL COUPLE.

229
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:32,011
- NICE TO BE BACK IN A QUEEN.

230
00:08:34,304 --> 00:08:36,807
IT'S TOO MUCH PRESSURE. 
- I CAN'T DO THIS.

231
00:08:36,807 --> 00:08:38,518
[narrator] 
SO LINDSAY AND TOBIAS

232
00:08:38,518 --> 00:08:40,728
FINALLY TOOK A HARD 
LOOK AT THEIR RELATIONSHIP.

233
00:08:40,728 --> 00:08:42,479
- YOU KNOW, LINDSAY,

234
00:08:42,479 --> 00:08:44,857
AS A THERAPIST, I HAVE ADVISED 
A NUMBER OF COUPLES...

235
00:08:44,857 --> 00:08:47,527
TO EXPLORE 
AN OPEN RELATIONSHIP...

236
00:08:47,527 --> 00:08:50,655
WHERE-WHERE THE COUPLE REMAINS 
EMOTIONALLY COMMITTED,

237
00:08:50,655 --> 00:08:54,491
BUT FREE TO EXPLORE 
EXTRAMARITAL ENCOUNTERS.

238
00:08:54,491 --> 00:08:55,785
- DID IT WORK 
FOR THOSE PEOPLE?

239
00:08:55,785 --> 00:08:58,203
- NO. IT NEVER DOES.

240
00:08:58,203 --> 00:09:00,915
THESE PEOPLE SOMEHOW 
DELUDE THEMSELVES INTO

241
00:09:00,915 --> 00:09:02,124
THINKING IT MIGHT, BUT--

242
00:09:03,751 --> 00:09:06,796
BUT IT MIGHT 
WORK FOR US.

243
00:09:06,796 --> 00:09:08,548
- WELL, WE COULD GIVE IT A SHOT.

244
00:09:08,548 --> 00:09:10,507
- GREAT. WE'LL HAMMER OUT 
THE DETAILS LATER.

245
00:09:10,507 --> 00:09:13,343
RIGHT NOW WE'VE GOT 
A DAUGHTER TO TELL.

246
00:09:13,343 --> 00:09:15,470
MAEBY, WE'RE HAVING 
A FAMILY MEETING!

247
00:09:15,470 --> 00:09:16,931
[narrator] 
ON HER WAY

248
00:09:16,931 --> 00:09:18,641
TO THE FAMILY MEETING, 
- FAMILY MEETING!

249
00:09:18,641 --> 00:09:19,850
[narrator] 
LINDSAY HAD

250
00:09:19,850 --> 00:09:21,101
AN UNEXPECTED ENCOUNTER.

251
00:09:21,101 --> 00:09:22,311
- HELLO.

252
00:09:22,311 --> 00:09:23,771
- OH, HI. 
GOB TOLD ME TO COME BY.

253
00:09:23,771 --> 00:09:25,355
- WELL, UH, 
I DON'T THINK HE'S HERE.

254
00:09:25,355 --> 00:09:29,484
- WELL, TELL HIM 
I LIKE WHAT I SEE.

255
00:09:29,484 --> 00:09:31,403
- AND WE PROBABLY WON'T 
EVEN ACT ON IT.

256
00:09:31,403 --> 00:09:33,530
WE'RE NOT 
GONNA GET A DIVORCE.

257
00:09:33,530 --> 00:09:35,324
IF ANYTHING, 
IT'LL BRING MOMMY AND DADDY

258
00:09:35,324 --> 00:09:36,617
CLOSER TOGETHER.

259
00:09:36,617 --> 00:09:38,285
- I MET SOMEONE. 
I'VE GOT A DATE.

260
00:09:38,285 --> 00:09:41,330
I'M DATING SOMEONE.

261
00:09:41,330 --> 00:09:47,169
- WELL, LET THE GREAT 
EXPERIMENT BEGIN!

262
00:09:47,169 --> 00:09:49,213
- YOU'RE NOT USING 
MY MASTER BEDROOM FOR THAT.

263
00:09:49,213 --> 00:09:50,923
- I BELIEVE YOU LEFT.

264
00:09:50,923 --> 00:09:53,175
OR DID YOU REALIZE HOW MUCH 
YOU NEED US AFTER ALL?

265
00:09:53,175 --> 00:09:55,135
- ACTUALLY, I CAME BACK 
BECAUSE I NEED SOMETHING.

266
00:09:55,135 --> 00:09:56,511
- HMM.

267
00:09:56,511 --> 00:09:58,222
- SOME THINGS.

268
00:09:58,222 --> 00:10:00,474
LIKE THE CHECKBOOK. 
WHERE'S THE CORPORATE CHECKBOOK?

269
00:10:00,474 --> 00:10:03,018
- GOB MUST'VE TAKEN IT 
TO THE OFFICE.

270
00:10:03,018 --> 00:10:04,812
MOM PUT HIM IN CHARGE.

271
00:10:04,812 --> 00:10:06,856
THAT'S RIGHT, MICHAEL. 
HE'S GOT YOUR OLD JOB.

272
00:10:06,856 --> 00:10:08,440
- WELL, I BETTER GET OVER THERE

273
00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:10,567
BEFORE HE BRINGS THE WHOLE 
COMPANY DOWN.

274
00:10:10,567 --> 00:10:11,902
- IT'S ONLY BEEN THREE HOURS.

275
00:10:11,902 --> 00:10:13,403
HOW MUCH DAMAGE 
COULD HE REALLY DO?

276
00:10:13,403 --> 00:10:15,197
AND RELEASE.

277
00:10:15,197 --> 00:10:17,407
[narrator] 
IN THREE HOURS, GOB HAD

278
00:10:17,407 --> 00:10:20,160
DONE $45,000 IN DAMAGE.

279
00:10:20,160 --> 00:10:22,121
- IN THERE, PLEASE.

280
00:10:23,873 --> 00:10:26,709
- HEY, WHERE'S MY DESK?

281
00:10:26,709 --> 00:10:28,585
- OH, I THINK 
IT'S THE MASSAGE TABLE

282
00:10:28,585 --> 00:10:30,796
IN THE BREAK ROOM NOW.

283
00:10:30,796 --> 00:10:32,673
TAKE THE WINDOW. 
- NO, HOLD IT.

284
00:10:32,673 --> 00:10:35,092
GOB, MOM MAY THINK 
THAT SHE'S GIVEN YOU MY JOB,

285
00:10:35,092 --> 00:10:37,386
BUT THE BOARD STILL HAS TO 
APPROVE THAT DECISION.

286
00:10:37,386 --> 00:10:40,765
- ACTUALLY, THEY ALREADY HAVE. 
- WHY SHOULD WE BELIEVE IN YOU?

287
00:10:40,765 --> 00:10:42,557
- FOR THE SAME REASON 
YOU SHOULD BELIEVE THAT

288
00:10:42,557 --> 00:10:43,768
A HUNDRED-DOLLAR BILL...

289
00:10:43,768 --> 00:10:47,146
IS NO MORE 
THAN A HUNDRED PENNIES.

290
00:10:47,146 --> 00:10:50,274
[gasping]

291
00:10:50,274 --> 00:10:51,942
THEY APPROVED ME UNANIMOUSLY.

292
00:10:51,942 --> 00:10:53,485
- WHY WOULDN'T THEY?

293
00:10:53,485 --> 00:10:55,237
YOU'VE ONLY LOST THEM 
$99 SO FAR.

294
00:10:55,237 --> 00:10:57,156
- I'VE ALREADY BEEN 
PRETTY SUCCESSFUL.

295
00:10:57,156 --> 00:10:58,532
SHOWING THE MODEL HOUSE AGAIN.

296
00:10:58,532 --> 00:11:00,200
SENT A REALTOR OVER THERE 
YESTERDAY.

297
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:01,744
[narrator] 
IT WAS THIS REALTOR

298
00:11:01,744 --> 00:11:03,453
WHO'D RUN INTO LINDSAY, 
THINKING SHE WAS

299
00:11:03,453 --> 00:11:04,872
LOOKING FOR A HOME.

300
00:11:04,872 --> 00:11:06,498
- I HAVE AN OPEN THING 
GOIN' ON TOO.

301
00:11:06,498 --> 00:11:08,333
I'LL GIVE YOU THE ADDRESS, 
AND YOU CAN COME BY.

302
00:11:08,333 --> 00:11:11,336
AND I THINK YOU'LL REALLY 
LIKE THE NEIGHBORS.

303
00:11:11,336 --> 00:11:13,255
- OKAY.

304
00:11:13,255 --> 00:11:14,757
- SO WHAT BRINGS YOU HERE, 
MICHAEL?

305
00:11:14,757 --> 00:11:16,508
I HOPE IT'S NOT 
FOR A HANDOUT.

306
00:11:16,508 --> 00:11:18,969
I RUN A PRETTY TIGHT SHIP 
AROUND HERE.

307
00:11:18,969 --> 00:11:21,764
- WITH A POOL TABLE? 
- IT'S A GAMING SHIP.

308
00:11:21,764 --> 00:11:25,392
- I'M HERE BECAUSE 
I THOUGHT YOU MIGHT NEED ME.

309
00:11:26,769 --> 00:11:28,979
- I NEED YOU? 
- THAT'S RIGHT.

310
00:11:28,979 --> 00:11:31,606
- OH, BOY, THAT'S GOOD.

311
00:11:31,606 --> 00:11:35,527
CAN'T WAIT TO CALL THE GUYS 
IN TO HEAR THIS ONE.

312
00:11:35,527 --> 00:11:37,654
LISTEN-- HOW DO YOU 
INTERCOM ON THIS?

313
00:11:37,654 --> 00:11:38,739
- STAR TWO.

314
00:11:38,739 --> 00:11:40,657
- YEAH. 
AT THE SAME TIME?

315
00:11:40,657 --> 00:11:42,326
- YEAH, JUST-- 
NO, THE STAR IN THE CORNER.

316
00:11:42,326 --> 00:11:43,368
THE STAR.

317
00:11:43,368 --> 00:11:44,787
- SO IF I DO IT LIKE THAT--

318
00:11:44,787 --> 00:11:46,496
- NO, TURN IT AROUND 
THE OTHER WAY. STAR.

319
00:11:46,496 --> 00:11:47,873
- OH, THAT STAR.

320
00:11:47,873 --> 00:11:49,666
- LET'S JUST HANG IT UP. 
THERE WE GO.

321
00:11:49,666 --> 00:11:52,127
I-I THOUGHT THAT YOU MIGHT NEED 
ME TO HELP YOU WITH THE BOOKS.

322
00:11:52,127 --> 00:11:54,004
YOU KNOW, 
THE CORPORATE CHECKBOOK.

323
00:11:54,004 --> 00:11:55,380
WHERE IS IT?

324
00:11:55,380 --> 00:11:56,757
- ACTUALLY, MOM'S GOT IT.

325
00:11:56,757 --> 00:11:58,550
SHE WASN'T COMFORTABLE 
WITH ME--

326
00:11:58,550 --> 00:11:59,885
[narrator] 
MICHAEL NOW HAD

327
00:11:59,885 --> 00:12:01,636
THE DISTASTEFUL CHOICE...

328
00:12:01,636 --> 00:12:03,764
OF EITHER ASKING HIS MOTHER 
FOR MONEY OR GOING TO JAIL.

329
00:12:03,764 --> 00:12:05,724
- MAYBE BUSTER 
KILLED HER ALREADY.

330
00:12:05,724 --> 00:12:06,892
[narrator] 
TOBIAS WAS ALSO

331
00:12:06,892 --> 00:12:09,144
HAVING A BAD DAY.

332
00:12:09,144 --> 00:12:11,814
LINDSAY HAD MET SOMEONE, 
AND HE HADN'T.

333
00:12:11,814 --> 00:12:13,816
AND THAT'S WHEN HE FOUND WHAT

334
00:12:13,816 --> 00:12:16,068
HE THOUGHT WAS A SUPPORT GROUP 
FOR DEPRESSED MEN.

335
00:12:19,780 --> 00:12:22,449
- WELL, IF IT ISN'T THE BOY 
WHO CRIED "PHOENIX."

336
00:12:22,449 --> 00:12:26,536
- OHH! NO, I WAS JUST, UH-- 
JUST WORRIED ABOUT BUSTER.

337
00:12:26,536 --> 00:12:29,790
I THOUGHT MAYBE I SHOULD 
GIVE HIM A LITTLE GUIDANCE.

338
00:12:29,790 --> 00:12:31,666
WRITE HIM A CHECK.

339
00:12:31,666 --> 00:12:33,752
BE A ROLE MODEL. 
WHERE'S THE COMPANY CHECKBOOK?

340
00:12:33,752 --> 00:12:35,587
- I ALREADY HAVE A NEW 
ROLE MODEL, MICHAEL.

341
00:12:35,587 --> 00:12:37,506
- HIS UNCLE OSCAR 
IS LIVING HERE NOW.

342
00:12:37,506 --> 00:12:39,758
- WOW.

343
00:12:39,758 --> 00:12:43,095
YOU GUYS HAVE ACCOMPLISHED A LOT 
IN THE LAST THREE HOURS.

344
00:12:43,095 --> 00:12:44,805
WHERE IS HE?

345
00:12:44,805 --> 00:12:46,306
- I SENT HIM OUT 
FOR A NEW AIR HORN.

346
00:12:46,306 --> 00:12:49,393
[bell dings] 
[men grunting]

347
00:12:51,020 --> 00:12:53,981
[ horn blasts ] 
- YEAH!

348
00:12:53,981 --> 00:12:56,233
- WE'VE GOT IT ALL 
UNDER CONTROL.

349
00:12:56,233 --> 00:12:57,401
- GREAT.

350
00:12:59,444 --> 00:13:01,030
I'M JUST WORRIED 
THAT IT'S ONLY GONNA BE

351
00:13:01,030 --> 00:13:02,614
A MATTER OF TIME...

352
00:13:02,614 --> 00:13:04,825
BEFORE THE MEDIA STARTS 
PUTTING TOGETHER ALL THE PIECES

353
00:13:04,825 --> 00:13:06,869
OF THIS IRAQ STORY.

354
00:13:06,869 --> 00:13:08,745
[narrator] 
MICHAEL HAD RECENTLY FOUND OUT

355
00:13:08,745 --> 00:13:10,247
THAT THE MODEL HOME...

356
00:13:10,247 --> 00:13:12,166
HE AND HIS SON 
CURRENTLY LIVED IN...

357
00:13:12,166 --> 00:13:14,334
WAS VERY SIMILAR TO SOME 
HIS FATHER MAY HAVE ILLEGALLY

358
00:13:14,334 --> 00:13:16,628
BEEN BUILDING IN IRAQ.

359
00:13:16,628 --> 00:13:18,463
- THEY HAVEN'T YET.

360
00:13:18,463 --> 00:13:21,091
AND FRANKLY, IT'S A VERY 
DIFFICULT CHARGE TO PROVE.

361
00:13:26,763 --> 00:13:29,975
- MAN, THAT JURY'S GONNA 
FALL IN LOVE WITH YOU.

362
00:13:29,975 --> 00:13:31,726
- WHAT DO YOU NEED, 
MICHAEL?

363
00:13:31,726 --> 00:13:34,604
- I DON'T NEED ANYTHING.

364
00:13:34,604 --> 00:13:37,691
I'M GREAT, 'CAUSE 
EVERYONE ELSE IS GREAT.

365
00:13:37,691 --> 00:13:39,401
I CAN'T TELL YOU 
HOW NICE IT IS

366
00:13:39,401 --> 00:13:41,778
TO NOT BE NEEDED ANYMORE.

367
00:13:41,778 --> 00:13:44,406
- I WANT YOU.

368
00:13:46,951 --> 00:13:51,121
- OKAY, THE JURY MIGHT 
ACTUALLY LIKE THAT.

369
00:13:51,121 --> 00:13:52,622
[narrator] 
IT WAS AT THAT MOMENT

370
00:13:52,622 --> 00:13:55,250
THAT GOB FOUND SOMETHING 
THE JURY MIGHT NOT LIKE.

371
00:13:56,293 --> 00:13:58,587
- HAMMER. 
OOPS.

372
00:14:07,930 --> 00:14:09,723
[narrator] 
AND LINDSAY ARRIVED AT WHAT

373
00:14:09,723 --> 00:14:10,975
SHE THOUGHT WAS A DATE.

374
00:14:10,975 --> 00:14:12,935
- HEY! 
YOU FOUND IT.

375
00:14:12,935 --> 00:14:15,604
SO, SHALL WE START 
IN THE KITCHEN?

376
00:14:15,604 --> 00:14:18,398
- I THOUGHT THE BEDROOM. 
- SURE.

377
00:14:18,398 --> 00:14:19,942
I'LL MEET YOU UP THERE.

378
00:14:19,942 --> 00:14:22,236
I GOTTA MAKE THIS PLACE 
SMELL LIKE COOKIES.

379
00:14:22,236 --> 00:14:23,570
AND YOU SHOULD KNOW,

380
00:14:23,570 --> 00:14:25,948
I AM ANTICIPATING 
MULTIPLES ON THIS.

381
00:14:25,948 --> 00:14:28,325
- WELL, I WOULDN'T BE 
DOING THIS IF I DIDN'T THINK

382
00:14:28,325 --> 00:14:29,659
THAT WAS A POSSIBILITY.

383
00:14:33,873 --> 00:14:35,665
[narrator] 
LINDSAY WAS NERVOUS

384
00:14:35,665 --> 00:14:37,542
AND TOOK A SHOWER TO RELAX.

385
00:14:37,542 --> 00:14:40,045
- I CAN'T DO THIS. 
I'M NOT READY FOR THIS.

386
00:14:40,045 --> 00:14:42,172
[screams]

387
00:14:42,172 --> 00:14:43,798
- COME ON, KIDS.

388
00:14:43,798 --> 00:14:45,842
WE'LL GO DOWNSTAIRS 
AND HAVE SOME COOKIES.

389
00:14:45,842 --> 00:14:47,052
[narrator] 
THE KIDS WERE IN

390
00:14:47,052 --> 00:14:49,388
FOR SOME BAD NEWS TOO.

391
00:14:49,388 --> 00:14:51,473
TOBIAS, MEANWHILE, 
DISCOVERED THAT WHAT HE THOUGT

392
00:14:51,473 --> 00:14:53,100
WAS A SUPPORT GROUP...

393
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:54,935
TURNED OUT TO BE A TEAM 
OF BALD MEN PAINTED BLUE.

394
00:14:56,561 --> 00:14:59,023
EVEN LUCILLE WAS ABOUT 
TO FIND HERSELF IN TROUBLE.

395
00:14:59,023 --> 00:15:00,274
- OH, YOU'VE DONE THIS 
BEFORE.

396
00:15:00,274 --> 00:15:01,816
- [chuckling]

397
00:15:01,816 --> 00:15:03,735
- YOU KNOW, YOU SHOULD LET 
YOUR HAIR GROW LONG.

398
00:15:03,735 --> 00:15:07,031
- YEAH? I'VE THOUGHT ABOUT IT. 
I GUESS I'D LOOK LIKE YOU.

399
00:15:07,031 --> 00:15:10,159
[chuckling] 
- MORE THAN YOU'LL EVER KNOW.

400
00:15:12,953 --> 00:15:15,372
- ARE YOU LIVING IN ONE 
OF SADDAM'S MANY PALACES?

401
00:15:15,372 --> 00:15:17,958
THEY MAY HAVE BEEN BUILT 
BY THE SAME DEVELOPER.

402
00:15:17,958 --> 00:15:19,668
AND A SEAL ATTACK.

403
00:15:19,668 --> 00:15:22,046
MEET ONE SURPRISED BATHER, 
COMING UP.

404
00:15:23,338 --> 00:15:25,632
- [giggling]

405
00:15:25,632 --> 00:15:27,717
[narrator] 
SEVEN MINUTES HAD PASSED SINCE

406
00:15:27,717 --> 00:15:29,428
GOB HAD DISCOVERED THE DOCUMENT.

407
00:15:29,428 --> 00:15:32,889
[intercom: woman] 
GOB, YOUR MOTHER ON LINE ONE.

408
00:15:32,889 --> 00:15:35,767
- I'M COMING OVER. 
DON'T TALK TO ANYONE.

409
00:15:35,767 --> 00:15:37,519
[narrator] 
IT WAS AT THAT MOMENT

410
00:15:37,519 --> 00:15:40,064
THAT LUCILLE WAS STOPPED 
BY A DOCUMENTARY FILMMAKER.

411
00:15:40,064 --> 00:15:42,232
- UH, YOUR COMPANY'S BEING 
ACCUSED OF PROFITING OFF

412
00:15:42,232 --> 00:15:43,900
THE BUILDING OF HOUSES IN IRAQ.

413
00:15:43,900 --> 00:15:46,111
- THAT'S CRAZY. 
WE'RE ALL LOYAL AMERICANS.

414
00:15:46,111 --> 00:15:48,572
- OH, YEAH.

415
00:15:48,572 --> 00:15:52,409
WOULD YOU ENLIST YOUR SON 
OR DAUGHTER IN THE ARMY?

416
00:15:52,409 --> 00:15:54,869
- YES.

417
00:15:57,497 --> 00:16:01,085
[narrator] 
MICHAEL WAS OUT OF OPTIONS...

418
00:16:01,085 --> 00:16:04,004
AND, KNOWING THAT HIS FATHER 
HAD A PENCHANT FOR HIDING

419
00:16:04,004 --> 00:16:05,589
VALUABLE THINGS IN WALLS,

420
00:16:05,589 --> 00:16:08,842
CONSIDERED ONE LAST 
DESPERATE GAMBIT.

421
00:16:08,842 --> 00:16:10,510
- THIS IS CRAZY.

422
00:16:10,510 --> 00:16:12,762
WHAT AM I DOING? 
USING A HAMMER TO TRY TO--

423
00:16:12,762 --> 00:16:15,890
- [yells] 
- [screams]

424
00:16:17,642 --> 00:16:20,354
ARE YOU CRAZY? 
- ARE YOU BLUE?

425
00:16:20,354 --> 00:16:23,815
- ONLY IN COLOR, MICHAEL. 
ONLY IN COLOR.

426
00:16:23,815 --> 00:16:25,442
IT SEEMS I MIGHT 
HAVE STUMBLED UPON

427
00:16:25,442 --> 00:16:26,776
AN ACTING OPPORTUNITY.

428
00:16:26,776 --> 00:16:28,903
- AS A MEMBER 
OF THE BLUE MAN GROUP?

429
00:16:28,903 --> 00:16:31,115
- OH, NO, YOU'RE THINKING 
OF THE SUPPORT GROUP.

430
00:16:31,115 --> 00:16:32,616
I MADE THAT 
SAME MISTAKE MYSELF.

431
00:16:32,616 --> 00:16:34,368
THEY'RE CALLED 
THE BLUE MAN GROUP.

432
00:16:34,368 --> 00:16:35,910
BUT IT'S FUNNY.

433
00:16:35,910 --> 00:16:38,413
IF I HADN'T 
SOUGHT OUT A SUPPORT GROUP,

434
00:16:38,413 --> 00:16:41,000
I NEVER WOULD'VE GOTTEN 
THIS GIG AS AN UNDERSTUDY

435
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:42,709
FOR A PERFORMANCE ART GROUP.

436
00:16:42,709 --> 00:16:44,836
[clatter on floor]

437
00:16:44,836 --> 00:16:47,547
YOU KNOW, THE UNIVERSE WORKS 
IN MYSTERIOUS WAYS, MICHAEL.

438
00:16:47,547 --> 00:16:50,217
YOU NEVER KNOW WHERE HELP 
IS GOING TO COME FROM

439
00:16:50,217 --> 00:16:52,094
UNTIL YOU LOOK FOR IT.

440
00:16:52,094 --> 00:16:55,264
- WHY DOES EVERYBODY THINK 
THAT I NEED HELP?

441
00:16:55,264 --> 00:16:58,350
- [chuckles] 
MICHAEL, LOOK AT YOU.

442
00:16:58,350 --> 00:17:00,935
I MEAN, YOU'RE HOLDING 
A SLEDGEHAMMER, YOUR SHIRT

443
00:17:00,935 --> 00:17:02,729
IS COV-- OH, I DID THAT.

444
00:17:02,729 --> 00:17:06,275
UM, HERE, LET ME, UH-- 
WELL--

445
00:17:06,275 --> 00:17:08,027
[narrator] 
AND MICHAEL REALIZED THAT

446
00:17:08,027 --> 00:17:09,444
HE, TOO, HAD BEEN TOO PROUD.

447
00:17:09,444 --> 00:17:11,905
- I NEED MONEY. 
- I CAN'T HELP YOU.

448
00:17:11,905 --> 00:17:13,615
- I KNOW.

449
00:17:13,615 --> 00:17:16,576
IT DID BOTHER ME THAT THEY 
DID SO WELL WITHOUT ME.

450
00:17:16,576 --> 00:17:18,953
BUT I-I DO HAVE TO 
ASK THEM FOR HELP.

451
00:17:18,953 --> 00:17:21,331
- AND I HAVE TO ASK 
FOR AN AUDITION.

452
00:17:21,331 --> 00:17:23,792
- YOU HAVEN'T 
AUDITIONED YET?

453
00:17:23,792 --> 00:17:26,253
- OH, NO, NO. 
I'M NOT IN THE GROUP YET.

454
00:17:26,253 --> 00:17:30,799
NO, I'M AFRAID I 
JUST "BLUE" MYSELF.

455
00:17:30,799 --> 00:17:34,344
- THERE'S GOTTA BE 
A BETTER WAY TO SAY THAT.

456
00:17:34,344 --> 00:17:36,055
[narrator] 
TOBIAS RUSHED TO THE THEATER,

457
00:17:36,055 --> 00:17:37,931
HOPING TO BE SEEN.

458
00:17:37,931 --> 00:17:40,059
UNFORTUNATELY, IT WAS DUSK, 
AND HE COULDN'T BE SEEN.

459
00:17:40,059 --> 00:17:43,395
[thumping] 
- WHAT THE HELL WAS THAT?

460
00:17:43,395 --> 00:17:45,314
[narrator] 
SO, FOR THE SECOND

461
00:17:45,314 --> 00:17:47,941
TIME IN TWO DAYS, THE FAMILY 
GATHERED AT THE HOSPITAL.

462
00:17:47,941 --> 00:17:50,569
- EVERYTHING'S GONNA BE OKAY. 
I'M SURE HE'S GONNA BE FINE.

463
00:17:50,569 --> 00:17:52,862
I'M SO SORRY THAT THIS HAPPENED. 
I SPOKE TO HIM JUST BEFORE

464
00:17:52,862 --> 00:17:54,948
HE LEFT THE HOUSE.

465
00:17:54,948 --> 00:17:56,158
- OH, REALLY?

466
00:17:56,158 --> 00:17:57,534
WHAT WAS 
THE LAST THING HE SAID?

467
00:17:57,534 --> 00:17:58,910
- I JUST "BLUE" MYSELF.

468
00:17:58,910 --> 00:18:02,038
- HE SAID SOME 
WONDERFUL THINGS,

469
00:18:02,038 --> 00:18:05,542
INCLUDING THE FACT 
THAT SOMETIMES PEOPLE...

470
00:18:05,542 --> 00:18:08,337
ARE TOO PROUD TO ASK FOR HELP 
WHEN THEY NEED IT.

471
00:18:08,337 --> 00:18:10,589
- OH, GOD! FINE. I NEED YOU! 
- I NEED YOU, OKAY, MICHAEL?

472
00:18:10,589 --> 00:18:12,591
- NO, I-I DIDN'T MEAN FOR--

473
00:18:12,591 --> 00:18:13,883
- HE WAS A REALTOR, MICHAEL.

474
00:18:13,883 --> 00:18:16,220
NOW MY HUSBAND'S 
IN THE HOSPITAL.

475
00:18:16,220 --> 00:18:18,472
- MOM VOLUNTEERED ME 
FOR THE ARMY JUST BECAUSE

476
00:18:18,472 --> 00:18:20,640
THE FAT MAN DARED HER TO.

477
00:18:20,640 --> 00:18:22,142
- WE CAN'T LET THEM TAKE BUSTER.

478
00:18:22,142 --> 00:18:24,936
- I LOST MY WIG, 
MY UNCLE SAM WIG.

479
00:18:24,936 --> 00:18:27,981
- MICHAEL, I AM SITTING ON SOME 
VERY HOT INFORMATION HERE.

480
00:18:27,981 --> 00:18:31,193
I KNOW TOO MUCH. 
I'VE GOT THE THINGY.

481
00:18:31,193 --> 00:18:34,321
HALF IN ENGLISH, 
HALF IN SCRIBBLY.

482
00:18:34,321 --> 00:18:39,118
- MICHAEL, PLEASE, 
WE NEED YOU!

483
00:18:39,118 --> 00:18:41,911
- WELL, I HATE TO CANCEL MY 
MEDICAL FOLLOW-UP IN PHOENIX,

484
00:18:41,911 --> 00:18:43,788
BUT YOU GIVE ME 
THE CORPORATE CHECKBOOK,

485
00:18:43,788 --> 00:18:45,039
I'LL SEE WHAT I CAN DO.

486
00:18:45,039 --> 00:18:47,417
- EXCUSE ME. 
MRS. FUNKE

487
00:18:47,417 --> 00:18:50,629
- OH, THIS GUY AGAIN. 
- HOW IS HE, DOCTOR?

488
00:18:50,629 --> 00:18:52,088
- IT, UH, LOOKS LIKE HE'S DEAD.

489
00:18:52,088 --> 00:18:53,757
- OH, MY GOD!

490
00:18:53,757 --> 00:18:56,135
- OH, LITTLE GUY!

491
00:18:56,135 --> 00:18:58,387
THE TEARS AREN'T COMING! 
THE TEARS JUST AREN'T COMING!

492
00:18:58,387 --> 00:18:59,721
- OKAY, OKAY.

493
00:18:59,721 --> 00:19:01,181
- UH, JUST TO BE CLEAR--

494
00:19:01,181 --> 00:19:03,683
LOOKS LIKE HE'S DEAD, 
OR HE IS DEAD?

495
00:19:03,683 --> 00:19:05,769
- IT JUST LOOKS 
LIKE HE'S DEAD.

496
00:19:05,769 --> 00:19:07,771
HE'S GOT, LIKE, 
BLUE PAINT ON HIM OR SOMETHING,

497
00:19:07,771 --> 00:19:09,606
BUT HE'S GOING TO BE FINE.

498
00:19:09,606 --> 00:19:10,857
- WHAT IS WRONG WITH YOU?

499
00:19:10,857 --> 00:19:13,109
- WHAT A-- 
[bleep] DOCTOR!

500
00:19:13,109 --> 00:19:14,736
- I'LL LET YOU 
CELEBRATE PRIVATELY.

501
00:19:14,736 --> 00:19:16,321
- HEY, WE WANT THIS COMPED!

502
00:19:16,321 --> 00:19:18,031
- WELL, I'M GONNA-- 
I'M JUST GONNA HEAD OUT.

503
00:19:18,031 --> 00:19:19,783
YOU DON'T NEED SOME, UH, 
PIECE OF-- [bleep]

504
00:19:19,783 --> 00:19:20,950
UNCLE HANGING AROUND.

505
00:19:20,950 --> 00:19:23,119
- HEY, HEY! THAT'S NOT MY DAD.

506
00:19:23,119 --> 00:19:25,455
THAT'S NOT THE GUY YOU WANT. 
IF YOU WANT ANYBODY, IT'S ME.

507
00:19:25,455 --> 00:19:27,207
- WHAT? 
- MICHAEL?

508
00:19:27,207 --> 00:19:28,833
- YEAH.

509
00:19:28,833 --> 00:19:30,377
I GOTTA TURN MYSELF IN 
OR MAKE BAIL,

510
00:19:30,377 --> 00:19:32,045
UH, MAYBE BY, LIKE, 8:00.

511
00:19:32,045 --> 00:19:34,381
HEY, HEY, HEY. 
THAT'S ENOUGH.

512
00:19:34,381 --> 00:19:36,049
WHOA, HEY.

513
00:19:36,049 --> 00:19:37,634
YOU MIGHT WANT TO 
HAVE THAT LOOKED AT.

514
00:19:37,634 --> 00:19:40,804
- THANKS, MIKEY. 
[kisses]

515
00:19:42,472 --> 00:19:44,849
- THEY THINK I'M INVOLVED 
IN THIS IRAQ THING,

516
00:19:44,849 --> 00:19:47,394
AND I CAN'T PROVE THAT I'M NOT 
WITH DAD NOT AROUND,

517
00:19:47,394 --> 00:19:50,021
SO I NEED YOUR HELP 
OR I'M GONNA GO TO JAIL.

518
00:19:50,021 --> 00:19:52,482
- WE'VE GOT THE PROOF, MICHAEL.

519
00:19:52,482 --> 00:19:54,859
DAD'S SIGNED CONTRACT 
WITH SADDAM.

520
00:19:56,195 --> 00:19:58,154
- [whispers] 
HUSSEIN.

521
00:19:59,448 --> 00:20:01,616
- USE IT.

522
00:20:01,616 --> 00:20:03,702
IF IT MAKES YOUR FATHER 
LOOK BAD, THEN SO BE IT.

523
00:20:03,702 --> 00:20:05,454
HE'S LONG GONE NOW.

524
00:20:05,454 --> 00:20:07,456
- HEY, UH, 
WHERE'S THE BRIEFCASE?

525
00:20:07,456 --> 00:20:09,249
- OSCAR HAS IT.

526
00:20:09,249 --> 00:20:11,793
- HEY, I'M AWFULLY SORRY 
I'M LATE.

527
00:20:11,793 --> 00:20:15,464
I GOT HERE AS FAST AS I-- 
OH, HOW IS HE?

528
00:20:15,464 --> 00:20:17,549
- DID YOU JUST 
CHANGE YOUR CLOTHES?

529
00:20:17,549 --> 00:20:20,302
- HEY, LOOK WHAT I FOUND 
ON WINDOWSILL.

530
00:20:20,302 --> 00:20:22,804
JUST HAT. 
SOMEONE TAKE WIG.

531
00:20:22,804 --> 00:20:24,514
[narrator] 
IN FACT, IT WAS GEORGE SR.

532
00:20:24,514 --> 00:20:26,182
WHO TOOK WIG...

533
00:20:26,182 --> 00:20:27,767
- HIT IT!

534
00:20:27,767 --> 00:20:29,769
AND WAS FLEEING THE COUNTRY 
WITH THE EVIDENCE...

535
00:20:29,769 --> 00:20:31,313
MICHAEL SO BADLY NEEDED.

536
00:20:33,357 --> 00:20:35,400
- YOU MADE A HUGE MISTAKE.

537
00:20:37,361 --> 00:20:38,403
[narrator] 
ON THE NEXT

538
00:20:38,403 --> 00:20:40,655
ARRESTED DEVELOPMENT.

539
00:20:40,655 --> 00:20:42,824
LINDSAY ALMOST STUMBLES 
UPON A DATING OPPORTUNITY.

540
00:20:42,824 --> 00:20:45,118
- YOU LOOK REALLY HOT.

541
00:20:45,118 --> 00:20:46,786
[narrator] 
BUT INSTEAD,

542
00:20:46,786 --> 00:20:49,873
IS ADMITTED TO THE HOSPITAL 
WITH A FEVER OF 104.

543
00:20:51,291 --> 00:20:53,918
MICHAEL FINALLY GETS 
THE CORPORATE CHECKBOOK,

544
00:20:55,587 --> 00:20:58,923
ONLY TO FIND THAT THE FAMILY 
HAS GOTTEN TO IT FIRST.

545
00:20:58,923 --> 00:21:01,092
AND BARRY LANDS IN JAIL.

546
00:21:01,092 --> 00:21:03,219
- YOU'RE GLAD TOBIAS 
IS PRESSING CHARGES?

547
00:21:03,219 --> 00:21:06,848
- I AM HAVING 
THE TIME OF MY LIFE.

548
00:21:06,848 --> 00:21:09,225
- HEY. 
- HEY, DR. HATE.

549
00:21:09,225 --> 00:21:11,185
- [guard] 
NO TOUCHING!

550
00:21:12,687 --> 00:21:15,231
- [exhales]
